Text.Value: There - a corpse like any other.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel slits Yenna's throat (off-screen). Yenna hits the ground, face wet with tears. A few guttural gasps, and she's dead. The rest of the party look on in horror. Lae'zel licks the blood from her blade.
EditorData.VFXTags: [WI] Splash of blood from the offscreen Yenna getting killed. Also some blood dripping from the blade afterwards

Text.Value: I didn't do anything!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player raises an eyebrow - this is more serious than they thought. Yenna panics.

Text.Value: Another normal evening in camp, I see.
Gortash warned you of this? Then there is nothing left to discuss.
No, please -

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel smiles - this has gone perfectly.
EditorData.NodeContext: Terror, cut off as Lae'zel cuts her throat

Text.Value: This is not the whelp who's been following us.
Blood and tears taste so sweet together. Ambrosia fit for Bhaal himself.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel slits Yenna's throat (off-screen). Yenna hits the ground, face wet with tears. A few guttural gasps, and she's dead. The rest of the party look on in horror. Lae'zel licks the blood from her blade.
EditorData.VFXTags: [WI] Splash of blood from the offscreen Yenna getting killed. Also some blood dripping from the blade afterwards

Text.Value: So Gortash spoke the truth.
Do it.
Let her go, Lae'zel. She's a child!
I saw her - she slipped into camp in the form of a woman and shifted into this... abomination.
We can't take the risk, Yenna. I'm sorry.
Let her go, Lae'zel.
Do not be deceived by her paltry form. This is no child. This is a shapeshifter who intends to slay us where we sleep.
Explain yourself, Yenna.
She doesn't seem to be putting up much of a fight...
You may lack resolve - but I do not.
Help me! She's gone mad!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Yenna struggles against Lae'zel's vice-like grip, unable to free herself. She spots the player -

Text.Value: You'd turn on me to save this ignorant whelp. Do I mean so little to you?
Is my word not enough?
Her wits are about her - she knows we outnumber her.
I shall cleave the truth from you like flesh from a dhour.
She tried to silence me and hide her deception.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel tightens her grip/shakes Yenna, silencing her. She points out a vicious cut along the side of her face.

Text.Value: Stay out of this. She is mine to purge.
Say your farewells, ne'voocrim!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Yenna whimpers as Lae'zel pulls her head back and draws a dagger, ready to slit her throat.

Text.Value: Kill her then - get it over with.
It's your decision Lae'zel. I want no part in this.
I-I just came to get warm! I - I like it here with you and -
What in the hells is going on here?
There's something we're not seeing here.
Then let us expose the truth through action.
I don't care if she's Orin or not. Kill her.
With pleasure.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [DG] Laezel (Orin) transforms into her true form.

Text.Value: Perhaps if I remove your eyes, you'll see things as they are.
Kainyank! Your deception ends now.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player enters camp. Walking into a secluded area (e.g. private room in Elfsong) they find Lea'zel gripping a terrified Yenna by the collar.

Text.Value: Do you have any proof?

Synopsis:
The first longrest in Lower City, Orin will abduct one of the players companion. (Laezel, Halsin, Gale or Minthara). Based on the players approval rating with them. (Friend, Good Friend and Romance) Highest approval will be the highest priority.

She will appear in camp impersonating her abducted victim and toy with the players. Shortly after, she grows tire of the game and reveals herself. And gives her ultimatum - Kill Gortash and retrieve his Netherstone - and bring it to her at her Bhaal Temple. Or the abducted companion dies. She will then teleport away.
